      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEWANA FAMILY (1) took the sit on the lead from a low draw but levelled up and led around the bend to score (30.07) at The Meadows in a Mix 6/7 FIN over 525m. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Looks the one to beat. BRAVE ISLAND (8) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.3 lengths at Sandown in a handy 29.61 beating Lisa Rose. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Sure to be thereabouts. RHYTHMIC ENERGY (7) struggled to get involved last start after settling well back at Shepparton, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at Bendigo (23.95) beating Piebald in a Grade 5 on June 19. Must be included in calculations. MINTER SCORCH (2) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
